Among his other publications were 
                The Stanford Achievement Test, 1923; 
                Children's Reading, 1925; 
                Sex and Personality, 1936; 
                Marital Happiness, 1938; and 
                The Gifted Child Grows Up, 1947.

scopecontent.p:
This box contains a fairly complete collection of Terman's articles, most present as reprints. There are a few books: 
                            Measuring Intelligence, Terman and Merrill, 1973; 
                            Memoirs of the National Academy of Sciences, vol. 15, 1921, containing the report of the committee at Vineland, N.J., of which Terman was a member; 
                            History of Psychology in Autobiography, vol. 2, containing an article by Terman, "Trails to Psychology," (an autobiography), 1932; 
                            Condensed Guide for the Stanford Revision of the Binet-Simon Intelligence Tests, 1920 by L. M. Terman; 
                            The Psychological Register, vol. 3, 1932, containing a brief biography and an extensive bibliography of Terman; 
                            Studies in Personality, 1942, a collection of articles contributed in honor of L. M. Terman; and several other books, not written by or for Dr. Terman, but once owned by him.
